              <section class="_yb_z547h0 _yb_1243rq0 _yb_1effwkc">
               <h3 class="_yb_yklevv _yb_1effwkc" tabindex="0">
                <div class="_yb_71yzpv _yb_1s8abj0 _yb_1effwkc">
                 <a class="_yb_c3orr2" href="https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/" tabindex="-1">
                  Life
                 </a>
                </div>
                <div class="_yb_33cyw3 _yb_w8fpaf _yb_1effwkc" tabindex="0">
                 <svg fill="none" height="20" viewbox="0 0 20 20" width="20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path d="M10.0011 10.6612L5.91234 6.57241C5.59699 6.25789 5.06949 6.25294 4.74754 6.57489C4.42228 6.90014 4.42393 7.41939 4.74506 7.73969L10.0011 12.9966L15.2588 7.73804C15.5742 7.42269 15.5791 6.89519 15.2564 6.57324C14.9319 6.24881 14.4127 6.24963 14.0916 6.57076L10.0011 10.6612Z" fill="#232A31">
                  </path>
                 </svg>
                </div>

               </h3>
               <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                Tesla stock is charging higher for a third trading session in a row as the company's robotaxi rollout gains steam and the war between CEO Elon Musk and President Trump cools off.

               </p>

            <div class="content yf-1jsv3x8">
             <a aria-label="Brazil's fiscal package to include higher tax on interest on equity" class="subtle-link fin-size-small titles noUnderline yf-17w8w6" data-ylk="elm:hdln;elmt:link;itc:0;ct:story;slk:Brazil's%20fiscal%20package%20to%20include%20higher%20tax%20on%20interest%20on%20equity;sec:topic-mid-section;g:576f1a8a-3ffc-3771-aa8a-31bc03acb28e" href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/brazils-fiscal-package-higher-tax-184741276.html" title="Brazil's fiscal package to include higher tax on interest on equity">
              <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
               Brazil's fiscal package to include higher tax on interest on equity
              </h3>
              <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
               <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
               BRASILIA (Reuters) -Brazil's Finance Minister Fernando Haddad said on Tuesday that the government's new fiscal package includes an increase in the income tax rate levied on so-called interest on equity (JCP) payments to 20% from 15%.  Speaking to reporters, Haddad said that the decision to include the measure - previously proposed by the government but not voted on by Congress - came at the request of lawmakers.  Haddad also confirmed that the fiscal package includes the unification of income tax rates on financial investments at 17.5%, replacing the current sliding scale of 15% to 22.5%, which varies according to the investment's holding period.
               <!-- HTML_TAG_END -->
              </p>
             </a>
             <div class="footer yf-1jsv3x8">
              <div class="publishing yf-1weyqlp">
               Reuters
               <i aria-hidden="true" data-svelte-h="svelte-sg6bkb">

               </i>
               1 hour ago
              </div>

                <a aria-label="Moody's flags risks from retail investors' push into private credit" class="subtle-link fin-size-small titles noUnderline yf-17w8w6" data-ylk="elm:hdln;elmt:link;itc:0;ct:story;slk:Moody's%20flags%20risks%20from%20retail%20investors'%20push%20into%20private%20credit;sec:topic-stream;subsec:fltrd-strs;cpos:5;g:22aa72c7-3d1c-34e4-84d0-dab5fb4dddde" href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/moodys-flags-risks-retail-investors-183336594.html" title="Moody's flags risks from retail investors' push into private credit">
                 <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  Moody's flags risks from retail investors' push into private credit
                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  The rush to court "Main Street" investors is transforming the traditionally institutional world of private credit, with asset managers launching new funds tailored to retail demand.  But the shift is also raising concerns about transparency, liquidity, and underwriting standards, as firms race to deploy capital amid limited supply of high-quality assets.  Private markets are gaining prominence as public listings have declined and more companies opt to delist, Moody's said, adding that with institutional investors facing capacity constraints, asset managers are increasingly turning to retail capital to sustain growth.
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_END -->
                 </p>
                </a>

                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  WASHINGTON (Reuters) -The U.S. Energy Department's loan office should fund oil and gas infrastructure, a White House aide said on Tuesday, as President Donald Trump's administration moves away from supporting projects designed to curb climate change.  "One of the big problems is, in the past the ... Loan Program Office has been used for a lot of these renewable projects," Jarrod Agen, a deputy assistant to the president and executive director of the National Energy Dominance Council, said at a Politico conference on energy.  The administration is changing the priority of the LPO, meant to help finance emerging energy projects that show promise but face difficulties getting bank loans.

                 <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  Drug pricing reform talks with US government lack clarity, industry executives say
                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  (Reuters) -Talks with the Trump administration about lowering U.S. drug prices have so far not provided clarity on when and how reduced prices will be implemented, top executives from Eli Lilly and Merck said at an industry conference on Tuesday.  President Donald Trump issued an executive order last month directing drugmakers to lower the prices of their medicines to align with what other countries pay.  According to the order, the administration was to set "most favored nation" price targets within 30 days.
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_END -->
                 </p>

                 <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  Shell's decision on Phase 2 of LNG Canada will depend on other opportunities, exec says
                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  Shell Canada's decision on whether to pursue Phase 2 of LNG Canada will depend on other opportunities that are available, President Stastia West said on Tuesday at a conference. LNG Canada, the country's first LNG export facility, is a joint venture between Shell, Petronas, PetroChina, Mitsubishi Corporation and Kogas. It is expected to ship its first cargoes by the middle of 2025.

                <a aria-label="Walgreens, Authentic Brands, Kourtney Kardashian among those evaluating Rite Aid assets, sources say" class="subtle-link fin-size-small titles noUnderline yf-17w8w6" data-ylk="elm:hdln;elmt:link;itc:0;ct:story;slk:Walgreens%2C%20Authentic%20Brands%2C%20Kourtney%20Kardashian%20among%20those%20evaluating%20Rite%20Aid%20assets%2C%20sources%20say;sec:topic-stream;subsec:fltrd-strs;cpos:21;g:7011e7c7-19f4-3e22-842d-720bb4547bd4" href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/walgreens-authentic-brands-kourtney-kardashian-172627561.html" title="Walgreens, Authentic Brands, Kourtney Kardashian among those evaluating Rite Aid assets, sources say">
                 <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  Walgreens, Authentic Brands, Kourtney Kardashian among those evaluating Rite Aid assets, sources say
                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  NEW YORK (Reuters) -Pharmacy chain Walgreens and reality star turned entrepreneur Kourtney Kardashian are among those picking over the remaining assets in Rite Aid's bankruptcy, according to two people familiar with the matter.  In addition to Walgreens, brand management companies Authentic Brands Group, WHP Global and Marquee Brands have been evaluating Rite Aid's intellectual property and potentially its loyalty program, according to the people who asked not to be named because the process is private.
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_END -->
                 </p>
                </a>

               <div class="content yf-1jsv3x8">
                <a aria-label="Meta to pay nearly $15 billion for Scale AI stake, The Information reports" class="subtle-link fin-size-small titles noUnderline yf-17w8w6" data-ylk="elm:hdln;elmt:link;itc:0;ct:story;slk:Meta%20to%20pay%20nearly%20%2415%20billion%20for%20Scale%20AI%20stake%2C%20The%20Information%20reports;sec:topic-stream;subsec:fltrd-strs;cpos:24;g:ddf11dae-2664-34bf-81cb-a6e354ebbf3d" href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/meta-pay-nearly-15-billion-171801208.html" title="Meta to pay nearly $15 billion for Scale AI stake, The Information reports">
                 <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  Meta to pay nearly $15 billion for Scale AI stake, The Information reports
                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  Founded in 2016, Scale AI provides vast amounts of labeled data or curated training data, which is crucial for developing sophisticated tools such as OpenAI's ChatGPT.  The deal, which has not been finalized yet, appears to be beneficial for Scale AI's investors including Accel, Index Ventures, Founders Fund and Greenoaks, as well as its current and former employees, the report said.  Meta, Scale AI and the startup's investors did not immediately respond to Reuters' requests for comment.
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_END -->
                 </p>
                </a>
                <div class="footer yf-1jsv3x8">

               <div class="content yf-1jsv3x8">
                <a aria-label="Bank of Mexico poised for 50 basis points rate cut despite inflation rebound" class="subtle-link fin-size-small titles noUnderline yf-17w8w6" data-ylk="elm:hdln;elmt:link;itc:0;ct:story;slk:Bank%20of%20Mexico%20poised%20for%2050%20basis%20points%20rate%20cut%20despite%20inflation%20rebound;sec:topic-stream;subsec:fltrd-strs;cpos:30;g:0902c227-e839-39de-ab8c-dd541b2b0920" href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/bank-mexico-poised-50-basis-171203015.html" title="Bank of Mexico poised for 50 basis points rate cut despite inflation rebound">
                 <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  Bank of Mexico poised for 50 basis points rate cut despite inflation rebound
                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  MEXICO CITY (Reuters) -Mexico's central bank is expected to cut its key interest rate by another half percentage point this month despite a recent surge in inflation, although analysts believe the pace of rate cuts could slow if prices remain under control.  In May, inflation exceeded the central bank's target of 3%, plus or minus a percentage point, after the headline rate accelerated to 4.42%, its highest level since November.  Core inflation, meanwhile, rose to 4.06%, its highest level in almost a year.
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_END -->
                 </p>
                </a>
                <div class="footer yf-1jsv3x8">
                 <div class="publishing yf-1weyqlp">
                  Reuters
                  <i aria-hidden="true" data-svelte-h="svelte-sg6bkb">

                  </i>
                  2 hours ago

                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  Content discovery platform Taboola (NASDAQ:TBLA) reported Q1 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 3.3% year on year to $427.5 million.                  <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  Tesla (TSLA) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  Shares of electric vehicle pioneer Tesla (NASDAQ:TSLA) jumped 3.5% in the afternoon session after tension between CEO Elon Musk and President Donald Trump continued to cool off. This de-escalation is likely a major relief for investors who had been worried about the potential negative impacts on Tesla's business, particularly regarding government contracts or regulatory scrutiny.
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_END -->
                 </p>

                 <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  Cracker Barrel (CBRL) Stock Trades Down, Here Is Why
                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  Shares of restaurant company Cracker Barrel (NASDAQ:CBRL) fell 5.5% in the afternoon session after the company announced a private offering of $275 million in convertible senior notes (debt) due 2030. The stock is likely down due to concerns about the dilutive effect of the notes, which can be converted to the company's ordinary stock, raising the total share count.
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_END -->
                 </p>

                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">

               <div class="content yf-1jsv3x8">
                <a aria-label="UniCredit disposals set to win EU nod for Banco BPM deal, sources say" class="subtle-link fin-size-small titles noUnderline yf-17w8w6" data-ylk="elm:hdln;elmt:link;itc:0;ct:story;slk:UniCredit%20disposals%20set%20to%20win%20EU%20nod%20for%20Banco%20BPM%20deal%2C%20sources%20say;sec:topic-stream;subsec:fltrd-strs;cpos:47;g:999d9a16-7cd1-3c49-8d7e-b8976835ed14" href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/unicredit-offers-sell-206-branches-165521581.html" title="UniCredit disposals set to win EU nod for Banco BPM deal, sources say">
                 <h3 class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  UniCredit disposals set to win EU nod for Banco BPM deal, sources say
                 </h3>
                 <p class="clamp yf-1jsv3x8">
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_START -->
                  BRUSSELS/MILAN (Reuters) -Italian bank UniCredit is expected to win European Union antitrust approval for its Banco BPM takeover bid after offering to divest 206 branches to ease competition concerns, people with direct knowledge of the matter said on Tuesday.  The European Commission, which acts as the competition enforcer for the 27-country EU, is keen on banking consolidation to create strong lenders in the bloc, one of the people said.  The majority of branches to be divested are in northern and north-eastern Italy and will be Banco BPM's, the sources said.
                  <!-- HTML_TAG_END -->
                 </p>
                </a>
